result.execSummary:
The defendant Trymane L Fraley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Trymane L Fraley is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Trymane L Fraley was found guilty of Manuf/Deliver Cocaine (>15-40g) [Modifiers: Repeater, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(cm)3.
  • Trymane L Fraley was found guilty of Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>15-40g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)3.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
Any other conditions as seen fit to be set by DOC.
To be taken from any prison wages available and remainder to be paid through extended supervision.

Defendant Trymane L Fraley in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Defendant Trymane L Fraley in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:32 PM. State - resolved - plead g to count #1 and #4 as alleged, #6 - dismiss outright, remaining counts to be dismissed and read in - recommendation of 10 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years ES, ES time is stipulated to but free to argue on the initial incarceration time. Voorhees agrees - comments that the time would be concurrent to each other and concurrent to a Milwaukee County Case 12CF1503 that he is being revoked on. Fraley agrees. Court dismisses count #6 and DRI counts #2, #3, #5, #7 and #8. Fraley pleads G to counts #1 and #4 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State offers exhibit #1 - copy of JOC from Milwaukee County Case #12CF1503. Court receives exhibit #1 after no objections (2:42 PM). State makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends 10 years in WI State Prison system with 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES for stated reasons - credit for 95 days. Voorhees makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends a lesser time in the WI State Prison System, previously mentioned that the time be served concurrent to Milwaukee County Case #12CF1503. Fraley makes statement, apologizes. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #4 - 10 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES - credit for 95 days, concurrent to each other and concurrent to Milwaukee County Case #12CF1503, with conditions of ES of: costs on each count - to be taken from any prison wages available and remainder to be paid thru ES, other conditions as may be set by P&P, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, submit DNA sample with expunction rights, $1600.00 seized by FOSO will be surrendered back to FOSO thru stipulation of the parties and release the other $400.00 back to the defendant, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, eligible for programs, right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on May 2, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Trymane L Fraley, in custody, in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:54 AM. State - here for ARGN. Voorhees has Information, waives reading of it, enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, sets for FPT, continues bond.  Final pre-trial scheduled for May 2, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Trymane L Fraley in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 1:59 PM. State - here for PH, originally filed as 16CF43 went through PH then was dismissed and this case 16CF55 was re-filed. State calls Tom Robinson, sworn in 2:00 PM. Voorhees asks for sequestration of all witnesses. State directs witness. Voorhees objection - speculation - sustained, 2:14 PM. Identification of defendant, 2:14 PM. Voorhees cross-examines, 2:16 PM. State - objection - sustained, 2:22 PM. State - objection - sustained, 2:25 PM. State - objection, irrelevant - sustained, 2:26 PM. Voorhees asks for leway in counts 4, 6 & 7. State objects - over ruled, 2:31 PM. State objects - sustained, 2:32 PM. Witness excused, 2:35 PM. State calls JM, sworn in, 2:35 PM. State makes court aware that the witness does have a case unrelated to this case that his attorney is aware of todays proceedings. Court advises witness of fifth amendment rights. Voorhees objects - sustained, 2:42 PM. Identification of defendant, 2:43 PM. Voorhees cross-examines, 2:44 PM. State objects - sustained, 2:46 PM. State objects - Voorhees rephrases the question. Witness excused, 2:51 PM. State asks court takes notice of prior convictions, Voorhees does not object. State files INFO, mirrors. Voorhees has motion for the court motion to dismiss count 6, for stated reasons. State makes argument to the motion. Voorhees makes statement. Court will not dismiss at this point for stated reasons. Court finds probable cause and binds over for trial. Voorhees asks for a continuance for the ARGN for stated reasons. Much discussion on allowing continuance. Court would like to proceed to ARGN and allow substitution of judge to be filed within 5 days. Court will now schedule ARGN for March 23 at 10:30 AM. Bond continued.  Arraignment scheduled for March 23, 2016 at 10:30 am.

Defendant Trymane L Fraley in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Defendant Trymane L Fraley in custody.   Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:26 PM. Court not sure why we are here today, believes it was to be in compliance with time limits for PH, matter is already set for PH, continues bond, adjourned.

Adjourned initial appearance at 03-07-2016 01:15 pm.
Preliminary hearing at 03-14-2016 10:00 am.

Defendant Trymane L Fraley in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Defendant Trymane L Fraley in custody and appears via video from FOSO.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:25 PM. State has filed a new complaint and stated reasons. New case # is 16CF55 - asking that bond on this matter be transferred to the new case and set this matter for another INIT on 3/14/16 at 10:00 AM. Court clarifies. Voorhees responds and requests a recess for stated reasons. Court would prefer to read the complaint and set the matter for a PH as stated by the State. Fraley asks for clarifications. Court responds. Court reads new charges and penalties for 16CF55. Court denies request for AIA and will set for a PH on 3/7/16. Voorhees again asks for the matter to be set for AIA. Court sets for AIA on 3/7/16 and PH on 3/14/16. State asks that the bond on this matter be set as the same on the new case. Voorhees responds, defendant is on a hold. State moves to dismiss this matter. State - bond - $10,000.00 cash on 16CF55.
